      Is visibility hidden better than display none?
      While "display: none" completely removes the element from the webpage layout, "visibility: hidden" only hides the element but keeps its position intact. This distinction is crucial when designing web pages with dynamic content or interactive elements.14 Jul 2023

      What is opposite to display none?
      The opposite of display: none in CSS is display: block or display: inline , depending on the type of element you are trying to show. display: none is used to hide an element, while display: block and display: inline are used to show elements.11 Jul 2021
